{
  "name": "Reference Data Generation",
  "description": "AI configuration for generating reference data options",
  "version": "1.0.0",
  
  "aiGeneration": {
    "model": "gpt-4",
    "temperature": 0.7,
    "maxTokens": 2000,
    "responseFormat": { "type": "json_object" },
    
    "systemPrompt": "You are a helpful assistant that generates structured data for business applications. You specialize in creating realistic, commonly-used options for dropdown lists and reference data. Always respond with valid JSON only.",
    
    "userPromptTemplate": "Generate {{count}} realistic and commonly-used options for a \"{{displayName}}\" dropdown list.\n\nContext Information:\n- List Type: {{displayName}}\n- Category: {{category}}\n- Description: {{description}}\n- Internal Name: {{name}}\n- Sort Preference: {{sortBy}}\n- Allows Custom Values: {{allowCustom}}\n\n{{#userPrompt}}Additional Requirements: {{userPrompt}}\n{{/userPrompt}}\n\nInstructions:\n- Generate practical, real-world options that users would commonly need\n- Each option should have a clear, user-friendly label\n- Values must be unique, URL-safe (lowercase, no spaces, use hyphens/underscores)\n- Include brief descriptions that explain when to use each option\n- Consider the category \"{{category}}\" when generating options\n- Make options relevant to business/enterprise applications\n- Ensure consistent formatting and naming conventions\n\nReturn a JSON object with this exact structure:\n{\n  \"options\": [\n    {\n      \"label\": \"Display Name\",\n      \"value\": \"unique_value\",\n      \"description\": \"Brief explanation of when to use this option\"\n    }\n  ]\n}\n\nRequirements:\n- Return only valid JSON, no additional text or formatting\n- Ensure all values are unique within the list\n- Labels should be professional and clear\n- Descriptions should be concise but informative"
  },
  
  "fallbackGeneration": {
    "defaultPattern": "generic",
    
    "patterns": {
